# Receipts OCR Tool — Development Rules

## Scope

- Build and maintain **receipt image → Document AI → editable table → CSV export** only.
- Do not add kakeibo reconciliation/matching UI until explicitly requested.
- Keep independent from the Parcel demo (`src/index3.js`) and `src/news/**`.
- Reuse kakeibo Google Sign-In (`src/kakeibo/auth.js`) for access gating; do not
  upload receipt tables to Google as part of login.

## Privacy (critical)

- Receipt images are sent to **Google Cloud Document AI** for OCR — this is intentional
  and must stay clearly disclosed in the UI and docs.
- **Never commit** real receipt images, OCR dumps, or exported receipt CSVs.
- **Never** store service-account JSON or long-lived API keys in the browser or repo.
  Document AI calls use a short-lived OAuth access token kept **in memory only**.
- Processor IDs / project ID / region are not secrets and may be stored in
  `localStorage` (`receipts:documentAiProcessor:v1`).
- Do not log access tokens or full OCR text in production UI paths; status messages
  should use file counts / error codes.

## Auth (Plan A)

- Gate UI with existing allowlisted Google Sign-In (ID token).
- Separately obtain a Document AI access token via GIS `initTokenClient` with
  scope `https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform`.
- Token must not be written to `localStorage` / `sessionStorage`.
- Clear the in-memory token on logout / 401.

## Soft spend guardrails

- Default monthly soft cap is `MONTHLY_SOFT_LIMIT` in `config.js` (not an Always Free quota).
- Always check `planBatch` / remaining quota **before** calling Document AI.
- Increment usage only after a successful Document AI response.
- Document that users should also set a GCP budget alert.

## Data model

- Core parsing/CSV helpers (`parseExpenseDocument.js`, `parseReceiptText.js`,
  `receiptCsv.js`, `quota.js`, `config.js`, `errors.js`, `documentAiClient.js`)
  must stay framework-agnostic plain JS (no DOM) where possible so unit tests can
  run under `node --test`. `oauthAccessToken.js` is browser-only.
- v1 granularity is **one CSV row per line item** (not one row per receipt).
- `receiptId` groups lines from the same image; preserve it on export.
- CSV columns live in `RECEIPT_CSV_HEADER` — keep export and docs in sync.

## Testing

- Add/keep unit tests in `test/receipts/` for parsers, CSV, quota math, and
  Expense Parser entity mapping.
- Use fabricated OCR / Document AI payloads only — never real merchant receipts.

## UI

- Separate Parcel entry: `receipts.html` → `src/receipts/receiptsApp.js`.
- Dependency-free browser UI (no frameworks), same visual language as kakeibo.
